From Stanley Uzoaru, Owerri The Imo State police command on Monday paraded suspects who murdered former aide to President Goodluck Jonathan and an All Progressives Congress (APC) chieftain, Ahmed Gulak on May,30,2021 along Ngor okpala/Mbaise road while on his way back to Abuja. Briefing newsmen ,the State police spokesperson, Michael Abattam on behalf of the State Commissioner of police, Muhammed Barde said beside killing Gulak, the gang have been responsible for various razing of police stations in the State and houses of prominent politicians . Also, the suspect responsible for razing the house of the President General of Ohanaeze, George Obiozor were also paraded.